Now let me analyze each fix:

**Fix 1 (Line 80):** `variant={ButtonVariant.plain}` — The type changed to add `'stateful'` to the union, but `plain` is still a valid value in both old and new types. No code change is needed for this fix — the value `plain` is still valid.

**Fix 2 (Line 76):** The `<Button>` contains only an icon element (`<MinusCircleIcon />`) as children. Per PF v6 migration, icon-only buttons should move the icon to the `icon` prop and make the element self-closing.

Current code (lines 76-83):
```tsx
<Button
  onClick={() => {
    onDelete(id);
  }}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
>
  {<MinusCircleIcon />}
</Button>
```

Should become:
```tsx
<Button
  onClick={() => {
    onDelete(id);
  }}
  variant={ButtonVariant.plain}
  icon={<MinusCircleIcon />}
/>
```

